<hr />
SAN FRANCISCO, July 22, 2013 ‚Äî NudeAudio, a new generation audio company whose founders have deep roots in product design, fashion and audio manufacturing, announce their global launch today with a range of portable speakers designed to fit listeners‚Äô various size, sound and ease-of-use needs.
 
A truly international brand, with design headquartered in San Francisco, operations headquartered in Hong Kong, and sales headquartered in High Wycombe, outside of London, NudeAudio‚Äôs first offering is the MOVE line ‚Äî portable Bluetooth speakers designed for people who believe that a premium audio experience and an affordable one shouldn‚Äôt be mutually exclusive.
 
Peter Riering-Czekalla, Chief Design Officer, states, ‚ÄúWe‚Äôve considered and challenged every detail. It‚Äôs as much about what we decided not to do, as it is about what we chose to embody in our products. Just because you can, doesn‚Äôt mean you should ‚Äî design takes restraint.‚Äù He continued to say, ‚ÄúIn order to deliver premium products at affordable prices, our approach is all about focusing on what matters most: streamlined features and functionality, aesthetic simplicity and prioritizing acoustics over marketing.‚Äù
 
One of the most distinctive design cues is a brightly colored carrying cord, available on all MOVE models, to emphasize and encourage ease of transport and the joys of sharing music, video, gaming and other audio-related experiences with those around you.  
 
The MOVE range features four speaker models and is currently available in two color sets: charcoal grey/coral, and light grey/mint. Borrowing from the fashion industry, the line comes in three sizes: S, M and L. The ‚ÄúMove S‚Äù is an ultra-portable pocket-sized version, which comes in both a Bluetooth and a 3.5mm variant. The ‚ÄúMove M‚Äù takes things up a notch in terms of both size and bass, and the ‚ÄúMove L‚Äù offers the range‚Äôs biggest size, which fills an entire room with rich, warm sound. All models come with a thick, durable silicone sleeve that‚Äôs both tactile and protective.
 
What makes the range particularly noteworthy is its dedication to high-quality sound and design while also being as economical and thoughtful about every decision, to deliver excellent standards at an approachable price point.

The MOVE line will be available from leading audio retailers starting in mid-August, 2013. Strategic retail partners in each region include DSG in the UK, XXX in the US, XXX in XXX.
The STUDIO line, a range of speakers for the home, is on track to launch from NudeAudio toward the end of this year. Stay tuned.

<code>[showhide type="post" more_text="READ MORE" less_text="READ LESS"]
Chief Marketing Officer, Tom Old adds, ‚ÄúWe‚Äôre thrilled to be able to put a line of speakers out on the market that can compete with the leading audio brands out there today ‚Äî at a lower cost to consumers. The category has seen a spike in over-premiumization, and we‚Äôd like to challenge that.‚Äù
 
Old continues with a few thoughts about today‚Äôs audio behaviors: ‚ÄúBluetooth speakers are now the most popular technology format and the preferred way for people to listen to music out loud from their smartphone or tablet. The benefits are obvious as it allows the phone to stay in close proximity of the user, so they can use other functions e.g. mail or Facebook while simultaneously listening to their music.‚Äù
 
NudeAudio CEO, Tom Dudderidge elaborates about the brand itself: "The Nude name embodies the values that have been central to everything we‚Äôve done from the very start and that‚Äôs to be minimal, simple and transparent while at the same time offering something refreshingly unexpected. We are extremely excited to bring NudeAudio to the world. This isn‚Äôt just another speaker.‚Äù
 
‚ÄúWe began with a blank canvas in order to bring a genuinely fresh design sensibility and norm-challenging approach to the traditional CE industry. Our mantra is ‚Äòpassionate about design, serious about sound.‚Äô Delivering on that promise is our key motivation. In addition to the positive feedback we‚Äôve received thus far, we hope that it will become self evident when you see ‚Äî and hear ‚Äî the products for yourself.‚Äù

